  // Creates a unique random id
  function createGuid() {
    return 'xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxyxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx'.replace(/[xy]/g, function (c) {
      var r = Math.random() * 16 | 0, v = c === 'x' ? r : (r & 0x3 | 0x8);
      return v.toString(16);
    });
  }

  function getCookie(cname) {
    var name = cname + "=";
    var ca = document.cookie.split(';');
    for (var i = 0; i < ca.length; i++) {
      var c = ca[i];
      while (c.charAt(0) == ' ') c = c.substring(1);
      if (c.indexOf(name) != -1) return c.substring(name.length, c.length);
    }
    return "";
  }

  // We start here by checking if we have any old cs (UserSession) else we create one by calling createGuid()
  if (getCookie('cs') == "") {
    var cs = createGuid() + (new Date().getTime().toString()).substr(5);
    document.cookie = "cs=" + cs + ";domain=thetop10sites.com;path=/";
  }

  // We register some href's to a tuple var and upload it to sessionStorage.
  // See also "call_beacon_js.html" comments, to understand how beacon works!
  var thisPage = location.href;
  var referringPage = (document.referrer) ? document.referrer : "none";
  var pc = createGuid() + (new Date().getTime().toString()).substr(5);
  var beacon_src = "https://thetop10sites.com/tracker/beacon.gif?sub=www?page=" + encodeURIComponent(thisPage) + "&ref=" + encodeURIComponent(referringPage) + "&ts=" + pc + "&cs=" + getCookie('cs') ;
  var sbeacons = JSON.parse(sessionStorage.getItem('sbeacons')) || [];
  sbeacons.push(beacon_src);
  sessionStorage.setItem('sbeacons', JSON.stringify(sbeacons));
  document.cookie = "pc=" + pc + ";domain=thetop10sites.com;path=/";

  function track_page(sbeacons) {
    if (sbeacons.length) {
      var lastBeacon = sbeacons.pop();
      var beacon = new Image();

      beacon.onload = function() {
        // update SessionStorage with sbeacons with last (and normally the only) element removed.
        sessionStorage.setItem('sbeacons', JSON.stringify(sbeacons.reverse()));
        // run the same method recursively to remove all the beacons and have only the last beacon_url.
        track_page(sbeacons.reverse());
      };

      beacon.src = lastBeacon;
    }
  }

  // user can change pages faster then the beacon is called.
  // it is called at the VERY end of the page load.
  // while the creation of the beacon (generating URL and putting it to sessionStorage) happens at the very beginning.
  var sbeacons = JSON.parse(sessionStorage.getItem('sbeacons')).reverse();
  track_page(sbeacons);
</script></body></html>
